{title: But For The Grace Of God}
{artist: Pat Boone}
{composer: Written by Jack Lebsock}

[G]A tramp on the street homeless and weak
Could be [D7]I but for the grace of [G]God

The steel of my soul could have weakened at best
Had [D7]I traveled the byways he's [G]trod

Oh [C]merciful Father oh [G]wonderful God
Thy [D7]Hands have spared me these [G]things
May my [C]heart know compassion
As a [G]child when she holds
A [A7]bird with a broken [D7]wing

[G]Dear Lord make me strong

Not to boast of my strength
But to [G7]lend it to the weak and [C]down trod
May I always remember things [G]dear to my heart
Are mine to hold [D7]only by the grace of [G]God


Dear Lord if it weren't for You

I could have been that poor tramp
Or sleep out in the [D7]alley tonight
Only for the grace of [G]God

I could have been born blind

With no eyes to see a wonderful world

That He made for us

Or I could have been born weak
And had to have [D7]somebody take care of me

For the rest of my days
[G]Thank You Lord
